summary: The document is an FBI record pertaining to the assassination of President John Fitzgerald Kennedy on November 22, 1963, in Dallas, Texas. It details an interview and a translated letter from ANGHEL DRAGOMIR, whose connection to the case is considered irrelevant. Additionally, it notes the participation of the Research Branch of the U.S. Embassy in Vienna, Austria, in the investigative process. The document was classified, with a review date of 04/15/1994, suggesting it underwent updates or redactions.
key_findings: The document is part of the FBI's records on the assassination of President John F. Kennedy.
It references an interview and a translated letter from ANGHEL DRAGOMIR, whose relevance to the case is deemed not pertinent.
Mentions the involvement of the Research Branch of the U.S. Embassy in Vienna, Austria, in the investigation.
The document was classified and has a review date of 04/15/1994, indicating it was subject to updates or redactions.
